### Expressivity  

The language of an unambiguous Turing machine is defined to be the same language that is accepted by the nondeterministic Turing machine. A language of strings \(L\) can be defined to be **unambiguously recognizable** if it is recognizable by an unambiguous Turing machine.  

The class of unambiguously recognizable languages is exactly the same as the class of [recursively enumerable languages](/Recursively_enumerable_language) (RE). Indeed, every deterministic Turing machine is an unambiguous Turing machine, as for each input there is exactly one computation possible. Therefore, all recursively enumerable languages are unambiguously recognizable. Conversely, every unambiguously recognizable language is recognizable by a nondeterministic Turing machine, and hence is recursively enumerable.  

The complexity class [UP](/UP_(complexity)) is defined as the class of languages that can be decided in [polynomial time](/Polynomial_time) by an unambiguous Turing machine.  

